We've all been there. The alarm screams, your eyes burn, and every cell in your body begs for five more minutes.

3
00:00:18,918 --> 00:00:30,809
But why is waking up so hard? Meet your Circadian Rhythm—a 24-hour internal metronome that dictates your energy.

4
00:00:30,809 --> 00:00:40,955
In the center of your brain, the SCN acts like an orchestra conductor, signaling the release of melatonin when the lights go out.

5
